msIdentifier.collection: John Frederick Lewis Collection of European Manuscripts

msContents.summary: This manuscript is a fifteenth-century German copy of the index to Pope Gregory I's Moralia in Job and Augustine of Hippo's Legenda sanctorum.

msItem.title: Index to moralia in job; Legenda sanctorum (Lives of the saints)
msItem.author: Gregory I, Pope, approximately 540-604
Augustine, Saint, Bishop of Hippo

supportDesc.extent: v+137+iii; 307 x 205 mm bound to 315 x 215 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto; earlier foliation in ink, upper right recto

layoutDesc.layout: Forty-to-forty-eight lines per page, double columns; initials, paragraph marks, underlining, and capitals touched up in red; unlined, with column guides in drypoint; written area: 233 x 145 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Initials, paragraph marks, underlining, and capitals touched up in red

history.provenance: Leander van Ess (1772-1847), Darmstadt; sold in 1824 to Sir Thomas Phillipps (1792-1872), no. 581; his sale, Sotheby's, London, June 6, 1910, no. 394, to Bull; John Frederick Lewis, Philadelphia; given by his widow, Anne Baker Lewis, to the Free Library of Philadelphia in 1936
